# Supabase Configuration (Required for all environments)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url_here
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# AI Service API Keys (Optional - app will work in demo mode without these)
VITE_OPENROUTER_API_KEY=your_openrouter_api_key_here
VITE_TAVUS_API_KEY=your_tavus_api_key_here
VITE_ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=your_elevenlabs_api_key_here

# Blockchain Configuration (Optional - for NFT features)
VITE_ALGORAND_NODE_URL=https://testnet-api.algonode.cloud
VITE_ALGORAND_INDEXER_URL=https://testnet-idx.algonode.cloud

# Subscription Management (Optional - for premium features)
VITE_REVENUECAT_API_KEY=your_revenuecat_api_key_here

# Custom Domain Configuration (Optional)
VITE_CUSTOM_DOMAIN_API_KEY=your_domain_api_key_here

# SECURITY NOTICE:
# 1. Copy this file to .env in your project root
# 2. Replace the placeholder values with your actual API keys
# 3. NEVER commit the .env file to version control
# 4. The .env file is already added to .gitignore for security
# 5. For production, use environment variables or secure secret management

# API Key Sources:
# - Supabase: https://supabase.com/dashboard (Project Settings > API)
# - OpenRouter: https://openrouter.ai/keys
# - Tavus: https://tavus.io/dashboard (API Keys section)
# - ElevenLabs: https://elevenlabs.io/speech-synthesis (Profile > API Keys)
# - RevenueCat: https://app.revenuecat.com (Project Settings > API Keys)

# IMPORTANT SECURITY NOTES:
# - Only VITE_ prefixed variables are exposed to the client
# - Supabase anon key is safe to expose (it's designed for client-side use)
# - Never expose service role keys or private API keys
# - Use different keys for development and production
# - Regularly rotate your API keys
# - Monitor API usage for unusual activity